<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>RamenOnline - Welcome to ROL</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <style>
    /* 1990s-ish AOL color theme */
    body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background: #C0C0C0; /* classic grey */
      font-family: Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;
      color: #000033;
    }

    a {
      color: #0000cc;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    /* Fake "browser chrome" bar */
    .top-bar {
      background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #004a9b, #003366);
      color: white;
      padding: 4px 10px;
      font-size: 12px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #001a33;
    }

    .top-bar-left {
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .top-bar-right span {
      margin-left: 8px;
      padding: 0 4px;
      border-left: 1px solid #336699;
    }

    /* Main layout */
    .page-wrap {
      margin: 10px;
      border: 2px solid #003366;
      background-color: #E5E5E5;
    }

    .page-header {
      background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #0066cc, #004080);
      color: white;
      padding: 8px 12px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
    }

    .page-header-title {
      font-size: 22px;
      font-weight: bold;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .page-header-subtitle {
      font-size: 11px;
      text-align: right;
    }

    .logo-box {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
    }

    .rol-logo {
      width: 50px;
      height: 50px;
      background: #0066cc;
      color: white;
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 26px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      border: 2px solid #ffffff;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #003366;
    }

    /* Content layout using a very 90s table */
    table.layout {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
    }

    table.layout td {
      vertical-align: top;
      padding: 8px;
      font-size: 12px;
    }

    .sidebar {
      width: 190px;
      background-color: #D8E6FF;
      border-right: 2px solid #003366;
    }

    .sidebar-box {
      border: 1px solid #003366;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      background-color: #F2F7FF;
    }

    .sidebar-title {
      background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #0072BC, #00518A);
      color: white;
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: bold;
      padding: 4px 6px;
    }

    .sidebar-content {
      padding: 6px;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    .button-link {
      display: block;
      margin: 4px 0;
      padding: 4px 6px;
      background-color: #FFCC33;
      border: 1px solid #996600;
      color: #000033;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 11px;
      box-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #CCCCCC;
    }

    .button-link:hover {
      background-color: #FFE066;
    }

    .content-main {
      background-color: #FFFFFF;
    }

    .content-box {
      border: 1px solid #003366;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      background-color: #FFFFFF;
    }

    .content-title {
      background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #0072BC, #00518A);
      color: white;
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: bold;
      padding: 5px 8px;
    }

    .content-body {
      padding: 8px 10px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .bullet-list {
      margin-top: 4px;
      margin-bottom: 0;
      padding-left: 18px;
    }

    .highlight {
      color: #006600;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    /* Footer */
    .page-footer {
      font-size: 10px;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 8px;
      background-color: #C0C0C0;
      border-top: 2px solid #999999;
      color: #333333;
    }

    /* Very 90s marquee strip */
    .ticker {
      background-color: #003366;
      color: #FFCC33;
      font-size: 11px;
      padding: 2px 4px;
      border-top: 1px solid #001a33;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #001a33;
    }

    .badge-beta {
      background-color: #FFCC33;
      color: #000033;
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-left: 6px;
      border: 1px solid #996600;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- Fake browser chrome -->
  <div class="top-bar">
    <div class="top-bar-left">
      RamenOnline Web Browser
    </div>
    <div class="top-bar-right">
      <span>File</span>
      <span>Edit</span>
      <span>Favorites</span>
      <span>Help</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ticker">
    <marquee behavior="scroll" direction="left" scrollamount="4">
      Welcome to RamenOnline &middot; A love letter to the golden age of dial-up Internet &middot;
      Surf. Slurp. Stay awhile.
    </marquee>
  </div>

  <div class="page-wrap">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="logo-box">
        <!-- Replace with your real logo image if you want -->
        <!-- <img src="rol-logo.png" alt="RamenOnline Logo" class="rol-logo-img"> -->
        <div class="rol-logo">R</div>
        <div>
          <div class="page-header-title">RamenOnline</div>
          <div style="font-size: 11px;">ROL Web Access Center</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-header-subtitle">
        Connected to: <span class="highlight">ROL Net</span><br>
        Experience the flavor of the 90s – now in your browser.
        <span class="badge-beta">BETA</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <table class="layout">
      <tr>
        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <td class="sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-box">
            <div class="sidebar-title">ROL Quick Links</div>
            <div class="sidebar-content">
              <a href="#" class="button-link">Start ROL Browser</a>
              <a href="#" class="button-link">Ramen Mail</a>
              <a href="#" class="button-link">Buddy Roster</a>
              <a href="#" class="button-link">Help &amp; Tips</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-box">
            <div class="sidebar-title">System Status</div>
            <div class="sidebar-content">
              <strong>Dial-up:</strong> Ready<br>
              <strong>ROL Servers:</strong> Online<br>
              <strong>Message Center:</strong> Idle<br>
              <br>
              <span class="highlight">Tip:</span><br>
              Double-click icons in the desktop client to open windows,
              just like the classic AOL software.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-box">
            <div class="sidebar-title">ROL Facts</div>
            <div class="sidebar-content">
              &bull; Inspired by AOL 4.0/5.0<br>
              &bull; Retro-themed web experience<br>
              &bull; Built for modern browsers<br>
              &bull; Crafted with extra noodles
            </div>
          </div>
        </td>

        <!-- Main content -->
        <td class="content-main">
          <div class="content-box">
            <div class="content-title">Welcome to RamenOnline (ROL)</div>
            <div class="content-body">
              RamenOnline is a <span class="highlight">web-based tribute</span> to the golden age
              of Internet access. Remember the first time you heard the hiss and screech
              of a 56k modem? The chunky blue toolbars, yellow running man, and portals
              full of news, chat rooms, and weird little corners of the web?
              <br><br>
              ROL brings that feeling back – not as a joke, but as a cozy
              nostalgia space where you can browse, chat, and check mail inside a
              retro-styled environment that looks like it rolled straight out of 1998.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="content-box">
            <div class="content-title">What is the ROL Web Browser?</div>
            <div class="content-body">
              The RamenOnline Browser is a faux-desktop experience that runs
              inside your modern browser. Once you sign on, you’ll see:
              <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li>A desktop-style hub with floating windows for Mail, Channels, and Chat.</li>
                <li>An AOL-inspired toolbar with colorful icons for <em>Read</em>, <em>Write</em>,
                    <em>Internet</em>, <em>Channels</em>, and more.</li>
                <li>A dial-up style <strong>connection animation</strong> (complete with sound)
                    that lovingly wastes a few seconds of your life, just like the old days.</li>
                <li>Internal mailboxes at <code>yourname@ramn.online</code> for in-world messages.</li>
              </ul>
              Under the hood it’s powered by modern web tech, but the
              interface is intentionally low-res, chunky, and a bit over-the-top:
              gradients, beveled buttons, and more blue than should be legally allowed.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="content-box">
            <div class="content-title">A Love Letter to the Golden Age of the Net</div>
            <div class="content-body">
              RamenOnline isn’t trying to replace your modern browser. It’s here for:
              <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li>Hanging out with friends in a buddy-list-driven chat world.</li>
                <li>Exploring themed “Channels” like Games, Tech, and Late Night Anime.</li>
                <li>Reading quirky messages and announcements in a handcrafted portal page.</li>
                <li>Reliving the vibe of logging in after school and seeing
                    <strong>“You’ve got mail!”</strong></li>
              </ul>
              The “ramen” part is a reminder not to take any of this too seriously.
              It’s warm, a little messy, and meant to be shared.
              <br><br>
              <span class="highlight">Plug in. Dial up. Slurp down.</span><br>
              Welcome to RamenOnline.
            </div>
          </div>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="page-footer">
    RamenOnline &copy; 20XX &mdash; A fan-made homage to the classic online service era.<br>
    All trademarks are property of their respective owners. ROL is not affiliated with AOL.
  </div>

</body>
</html>
